<h2><a name="vprintf_vfprintf_and_vsprintf" id="vprintf_vfprintf_and_vsprintf">vprintf, vfprintf, and vsprintf</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdarg&gt;</span>
    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vfprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vsprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>buffer<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

These functions are very much like printf(), fprintf(), and sprintf(). The
difference is that the argument list is a pointer to a list of arguments.
va_list is defined in cstdarg, and is also used by <a href="../other/va_arg" class="wikilink1" title="c:other:va_arg">va_arg</a>. For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">void</span> error<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>fmt<span class="sy0">,</span> ... <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
       va_list args;
       va_start<span class="br0">&#40;</span> args<span class="sy0">,</span> fmt <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       fprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> stderr<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Error: &quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       vfprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> stderr<span class="sy0">,</span> fmt<span class="sy0">,</span> args <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       fprintf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> stderr<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;<span class="es0">\n</span>&quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       va_end<span class="br0">&#40;</span> args <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       exit<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="nu0">1</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
</div>
<!-- SECTION "vprintf, vfprintf, and vsprintf" [3-] --></div>
